Shaman of 34 Winters <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/uleetahdarkwood.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Leetah Darkwood</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Froglok Guk Knight</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(9/16/01 7:42:15 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home.maine.rr.com/mabandwags/images/leetah.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tip your local Porter please.</span><hr size=1> I would like to know what is acceptable.  I read these posts and I look at some of the amounts that are given and I think, wow, I have been underpaying the druids I have gotten ports from.<br>
<br>
When I need a port usually, I do an /ooc WTB port to locationname.<br>
<br>
I then usually pay 10pp.  If the location is somewhere like Velious or Kunark then I would try and pay 20pp or more.<br>
<br>
After reading this post I am willing to change these prices a little.<br>
<br>
I think that as I get higher and higher level I am able to pay more.  <br>
<br>
The price you expect to receive should depend a little on the level. <br>
<br>
Everyone talks about twinks running around.  Not everyone is a twink.  It hurts when you say pay 100pp for a port and I am just not able to do that.  I want to be fair with my pricing,  and I have paid that much for a port, but I can only afford to do that once a week before I bust my bank account.<br>
<br>
I spend the money I make from experience groups on peridots and ports.  If a cleric that is not in my group rezzes me or one of my friends, I like to give them peridots.  I also give peridots and cash loot to the clerics in my experience groups.<br>
<br>
I never accept donations for sows or binds.  I always try and bind someone if I am playing a character that can do this.  I know that if you cannot bind, then you are stuck until someone binds you.  As a ranger, I always call out WTB bind when needed.  I usually pay 10pp.  In FV people usually take the money.  In Thurgadin, people always cancel.  I must admit, I get a little sad when I am calling out for a bind for 30 minutes in FV when there are tons of people that can bind.  I figure that a few are busy doing something else, but everyone?  Once I had a friend waiting for me at kc for a group.  I was calling out and was really frustrated at all the people that could bind hanging around the bank.  I just wanted to see how busy people were..  After about 4 /ooc's of WTB bind and WTB a bind please =), I did an /ooc of WTB bind paying 50pp.  I got my bind..  the person excepted the pp, but boy was my day ruined.  =/<br>
<br>
Daku – I really like your advice on stones for Wizards.  Until a week ago, I had no idea that it cost a stone to x-locate.  I will look up that stone and start carrying stacks of those one me as well as peridots.<br>
<br>
Most of the times when I have had someone x-locate me somewhere, I don’t even have a chance to donate.  I hit follow then when I try to get my money out to hand to them, it says they are busy (casting the spell) or the little box comes up asking me if I want the x-locate.  By the time I am at my location, they have already disbanded me.  If I haven’t said thank you yet, then I scroll up and see what there name is and send them a tell.  I haven’t really received that many x-locates, but now that I know about this stone thing, I will try and donate before I hit follow.<br>
<br>
Radjan – You said “A &quot;Thank you&quot; would be nice. (Note: &quot;thx&quot; &quot;thks&quot; and &quot;ty&quot; are NOT adequate substitutes... if I take the time to port you or rez you, then please take the time to type a couple of extra letters.)”<br>
<br>
The problem with this is that your definition of a word can be different from someone else’s definition.  To you, “ty” may mean “I am too lazy to type thank you”, whereas to the person typing it, it means “Thank you”.  How in the world are they going to know that this word has a different meaning to you?  How will they know that it offends you?<br>
<br>
Remember that EQ has its own little language.  There are people in the game that only know English as a second language, and there are others who just can’t type very fast.  Some people, after playing for so long, just use the words they see used so often.<br>
<br>
It is kind of like if when you go to another part of the country or world and pick up on the local accent.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
